{
  "texts": [
    "Each student peer assessed two other students and assignments were also marked by teachers.",
    "All students and teaching staff were involved in determining the criteria to be used in marking, and the weighting to be attached to each criterion.",
    "The system automatically computed the final criteria weightings using fuzzy decision theory.",
    "The paper also provided data on the reliability of peer assessment and outlined student and staff reaction to its introduction.",
    "Capuano et al. (2017) proposed a new model for ordinal peer assessment based on the principles of fuzzy group decision making."
  ]
}